2.10	KBUC	KBUC	KBUC (102.1 FM, "Super Tejano") is a radio station broadcasting a tejano music format. Licensed to Raymondville, Texas, USA, the station serves the McAllen-Brownsville-Harlingen area. The station is currently owned by Border Media Partners, LLC through its licensee BMP RGV License Company, L.P., and features programming from Citadel Media. The station has obtained a construction permit from the FCC for a power increase to 37,000 watts. KBUC also serves as the flagship station for the Rio Grande Valley Killer Bees. KBUC formerly broadcaster a country music format but flipped on August 15, 2011 at 5:00 p.m.	
